Question 1:
In your own words, what is the difference between frontend and backend web development? If you were hired to work on backend programming for a web application, what kinds of operations would you be working on?
---
Frontend is everything the client sees. This can be from text, buttons, to images loaded on the screen. Backend is the data being transfered, functions behind the scenes and everything that isn't directed rendered on screen.
Most of the backend work you would be working are would be API, Data, and other information based code. The basic structure of how the data and mechanisms of the website work.

